(secondQuint)Medium Term Outcome of Nonoperative Treatment After Achilles Tendon Rupture.

.

 30 patients suffering from acute Achilles tendon rupture was originally randomized to each arm, and followed up after 6 and 12 months.

 Of these a total of 56 patients was included in the final analysis, and invited to participate in this additional follow-up, 4-5 years after their original injury.

 Originally patients was monitored using: ATRS questionnaires, ATRA: Achilles Tendon Resting Angle, Heel Raise Work: number of lifts, lift height and total work, and tests of strength and stiffness in the ankle using a kinetic dynamometer.

